德弗里斯的节目播出后，贝丝认为录像带中反映的情况应该是真实的。她在接受《[[纽约邮报|纽约邮报]]》采访时称，如果范德斯洛特当时求救，她的女儿这时很可能还活着。她认为范德斯洛特把她女儿的尸体扔进了[[加勒比海|加勒比海]]，而且当时霍洛威有可能还没死。<ref name="Fox News 2008-02-05">{{cite news | title = Holloway's Anguished Mother: Tape Confession Means Natalee Could Have Been Saved | accessdate = 2016-06-05 | date = 2008-02-05 | publisher = Fox News Channel | url = http://www.foxnews.com/story/2008/02/05/holloway-anguished-mother-tape-confession-means-natalee-could-have-been-saved.html | archivedate = 2016-03-06 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160306183237/http://www.foxnews.com/story/2008/02/05/holloway-anguished-mother-tape-confession-means-natalee-could-have-been-saved.html }}</ref>贝丝还称，范德斯洛特当晚是打电话给父亲保卢斯，再由他“精心策划下一步该怎么做<ref name="Deadlineclose">{{cite news | title = Deadline for Van der Sloot close, Natalee's parents worried strings being pulled | date = 2008-02-12 | publisher = NBC 13}}</ref>。”贝丝和戴夫·霍洛威都声称约兰·范德斯洛特受到“法律的特别优待<ref name="Deadlineclose" />。”上诉法院驳回检察官的上诉，拒绝再度批捕范德斯洛特后，贝丝又表示她对范德斯洛特的人生仿佛人间地狱感到欣慰<ref name="NBC 13 2008-02-15">{{cite news |archiveurl=https://archive.li/20070703065557/http://www.nbc13.com/gulfcoastwest/vtm/news.apx.-content-articles-VTM-2008-02-15-0020.html |archivedate=2007-07-03 |deadurl=yes |url=http://www.nbc13.com/gulfcoastwest/vtm/news.apx.-content-articles-VTM-2008-02-15-0020.html |title=Natalee Holloway's parents still have hope for justice |accessdate=2009-04-24 |date=2008-02-15 |publisher=NBC 13 }}</ref>，之后还称希望约兰身陷《[[午夜快车|午夜快车]]》中那样的监狱<ref name="Fox News 2008-11-19">{{cite news | url = http://www.foxnews.com/story/2008/11/19/natalee-holloway-mom-aruba-investigators-not-following-up-on-any-leads.html | title = Natalee Holloway's mom: Aruba investigators 'not following up on any leads' | accessdate = 2016-06-05 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160306022059/http://www.foxnews.com/story/2008/11/19/natalee-holloway-mom-aruba-investigators-not-following-up-on-any-leads.html | date = 2008-11-19 | publisher = Fox News Channel | archivedate = 2016-03-06 | deadurl = no }}</ref>。

女儿失踪后，贝丝·霍洛威组建[[非营利组织|非营利组织]]国际安全旅游基金会<ref name="Fox News 2007-01-05">{{cite news | title = Natalee Holloway's Stepfather Seeks Divorce | date = 2007-01-05 | publisher = Fox News Channel | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160313225540/http://www.foxnews.com/story/2007/01/05/natalee-holloway-stepfather-seeks-divorc-1672658556.html | accessdate = 2016-06-05 | deadurl = no | archivedate = 2016-03-13 | url = http://www.foxnews.com/story/2007/01/05/natalee-holloway-stepfather-seeks-divorc-1672658556.html }}</ref>，旨在“告知并教导公众，帮助他们更加安全地出国旅行”<ref name="ISTF Mission">{{cite web | archivedate = 2008-05-02 | title = About ISTF: Our Mission | accessdate = 2008-05-02 | publisher = The International Safe Travels Foundation | deadurl = yes | url = http://www.internationalsafetravelsfoundation.org/MS/MS37/page.php?p=418 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20080502162007/http://www.internationalsafetravelsfoundation.org/MS/MS37/page.php?p=418 }}</ref>。她还通过纳什维尔讲师团发布广告，以公共演说自我推销<ref name="Nashville Speakers Bureau, Beth Holloway">{{cite web | url = http://www.nashvillespeakers.com/espeakers/8970/BethHolloway.html | publisher = Nashville Speakers Bureau | title = Beth Holloway | deadurl = yes | archivedate = 2008-12-04 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20081204225749/http://www.nashvillespeakers.com/espeakers/8970/BethHolloway.html | access-date = 2016-06-05 }}</ref>。

2010年4月，贝丝宣布名为“求救360”（{{lang|en|Mayday 360}}）的服务计划，旨在立即为在海外陷入困境的年轻人提供帮助。她还称，如有必要，会出动对相应国家有具体了解的前联邦探员前往协助。<ref name="NYPost 2010-04-05">{{cite news | title = Natalee Holloway's mom teams up with security team | accessdate = 2016-06-05 | first = Philip | last = Messing | date = 2010-04 | work = [[纽约邮报|The New York Post]] | archivedate = 2016-03-06 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160306082523/http://nypost.com/2010/04/05/natalee-holloways-mom-teams-up-with-security-team/ | url = http://nypost.com/2010/04/05/natalee-holloways-mom-teams-up-with-security-team/ | deadurl = no }}</ref>2010年5月，贝丝宣布娜塔莉·霍洛威资源中心会在位于[[华盛顿哥伦比亚特区|华盛顿哥伦比亚特区]]的[[美国国家犯罪与刑罚博物馆|美国国家犯罪与刑罚博物馆]]设立，该中心于6月8日起开放，旨在向失踪人士的家人提供帮助<ref name="AP 2010-05-28">{{cite news | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160303200037/http://blog.al.com/spotnews/2010/05/mother_opening_natalee_hollowa.html | url = http://blog.al.com/spotnews/2010/05/mother_opening_natalee_hollowa.html | title = Mother opening Natalee Holloway center to aid families with members missing, in trouble | accessdate = 2016-06-05 | date = 2010-05-28 | publisher = Alabama Media Group | agency = Associated Press | archivedate = 2016-03-03 }}</ref>。

虽然贝丝·霍洛威在案情出现新进展后又多次在电视上露面，但应联邦调查局要求，她不再在节目中谈论女儿或斯蒂芬妮·塔蒂亚娜·弗洛雷斯·拉米雷斯被害案的案情<ref name="WTOK-center">{{cite web | publisher = WTOK-TV | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160306093137/http://www.wtok.com/news/headlines/95916024.html | deadurl = yes | url = http://www.wtok.com/news/headlines/95916024.html | title = Natalee Holloway Resource Center Opens | date = 2010-06-08 | accessdate = 2016-06-06 | archivedate = 2016-03-06 }}</ref>。

== 针对案情调查过程的批评 ==
[[File:NataleeHollowayWall-female.jpg|thumb]]

特威蒂一家及其支持者批评阿鲁巴警方在案件调查方面缺乏进展<ref name="Geiss 2005-10-06">{{cite web |last=Geiss |first=Chuck |archiveurl=https://archive.li/20120630130650/http://www.bwcitypaper.com/1editorialbody.lasso?-token.folder=2005-10-06&-token.story=140221.112112&-token.subpub= |archivedate=2012-06-30 |accessdate=2016-06-06 |deadurl=yes |url=http://www.bwcitypaper.com/1editorialbody.lasso?-token.folder=2005-10-06&-token.story=140221.112112&-token.subpub= |title=Publisher's notebook |date=2005-10-06 |publisher=Black & White, Birmingham's City Paper }}</ref><ref name="CDNNCott">{{cite web | url = http://www.cdnn.info/news/travel/t051110.html | title = National Coalition of Victims in Action urges tourists to boycott Aruba | accessdate = 2008-10-13 | date = 2005-11-10 | publisher = Cyber Diver News Network | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20081013101315/http://www.cdnn.info/news/travel/t051110.html | archivedate = 2008-10-13 | quote = Senator Shelby stated in a letter, 'From all appearances, this investigation has been plagued with inconsistencies and conflicting information'. | deadurl = yes }}</ref>。但是，特威蒂一家在阿鲁巴的作为也受到批评，称他们极力掩盖任何可能对霍洛威品格形象不利的证据，不但要求她的同学对案情保持沉默，还多次在媒体访谈过程中宣扬他们对案情的看法，但特威蒂一家否认上述指控<ref name="Vanity" />。

特威蒂一家起初并不倡导抵制阿鲁巴旅游业的立场，但这种情况在2005年9月发生变化。贝丝此时呼吁人们不要前往阿鲁巴或其它荷兰领地旅游，称这些地方对游客存在安全问题。[[阿拉巴马州州长|阿拉巴马州州长]][[鲍勃·赖利|鲍勃·赖利]]也于2005年11月8日在新闻发布会上表态支持特威蒂，呼吁该州居民及其他人抵制阿鲁巴。<ref name="USA Today 2005-11-21" />赖利还致信其他多个州的州长寻求支持，[[乔治亚州|乔治亚州]]和[[阿肯色州|阿肯色州]]州长之后同样加入呼吁人们抵制阿鲁巴的行列。[[宾夕法尼亚州|宾夕法尼亚州]]费城市议会经投票表决，要求州长公开呼吁抵制，<ref name="Jamaica Observer 2005-11-11">{{cite web | title = Aruba boycott over missing teen case may spread to Philadelphia | date = 2005-11-11 | work = Jamaica Observer | url = http://www.jamaicaobserver.com/news/html/20051110T190000-0500_92210_OBS_ARUBA_BOYCOTT_OVER_MISSING_TEEN_CASE_MAY_SPREAD_TO_PHILADELPHIA.asp | accessdate = 2007-04-28 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20080222003813/http://www.jamaicaobserver.com/news/html/20051110T190000-0500_92210_OBS_ARUBA_BOYCOTT_OVER_MISSING_TEEN_CASE_MAY_SPREAD_TO_PHILADELPHIA.asp | archivedate = 2008-02-22 | deadurl = yes }}</ref>但州长没有同意，抵制活动也没有得到联邦层面支持<ref name="USA Today 2005-11-21" /><ref name="NatSupport" />。

阿拉巴马州的部分国会议员也支持抵制活动，其中包括代表芒廷布鲁克所在第六国会选区的[[共和党_(美国)|共和党]]联邦众议员[[斯宾塞·巴卡斯|斯宾塞·巴卡斯]]，他还曾在[[亚拉巴马州参议院|亚拉巴马州参议院]]和[[亚拉巴马州众议院|众议院]]任职。联邦参议员[[理查·谢尔比|理查·谢尔比]]也在写给[[美国旅行社协会|美国旅行社协会]]的信中表态支持抵制。<ref name="RitaTranCott">{{cite news | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160308140046/http://www.nbcnews.com/id/10639915/ | archivedate = 2016-03-08 | url = http://www.nbcnews.com/id/10639915/ | title = Transcript of 'Rita Cosby Live & Direct' for December 28 | accessdate = 2016-06-06 | date = 2005-12-29 | publisher = NBCNews.com }}</ref>谢尔比称：“站在我们人民的安全和福祉角度考虑，我觉得我们无法相信自己身在阿鲁巴时会得到（妥善）保护<ref name="RitaTranCott" />。”阿鲁巴总理奥杜维尔表示，阿鲁巴侦察人员已竭尽全力破解谜团，称美国方面的抵制“是荒谬可笑且不负责任的行为。我们不是游击队，也不是恐怖分子，我们不会对美国或是阿拉巴马州构成威胁<ref name="Oduber">{{cite news | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20121102121053/http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/travel/news/2005-11-09-aruba-boycott_x.htm | url = http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/travel/news/2005-11-09-aruba-boycott_x.htm | title = Aruba's prime minister condemns boycott call over Holloway case | accessdate = 2008-03-10 | date = 2005-11-09 | work = USA Today | archivedate = 2012-11-02 | publisher = Gannett }}</ref>。”

阿鲁巴酒店和旅游协会、阿鲁巴旅游局、阿鲁巴招待和安全基金会、阿鲁巴商会，以及包括公关部代表鲁本·特拉朋伯格（{{lang|en|Ruben Trapenberg}}）在内的多名政府官员组成“阿鲁巴战略传播工作组”，集体应对那些他们认为针对阿鲁巴且毫无根据的负面说辞<ref name="Aruba.com taskforce">{{cite web | archivedate = 2006-04-22 | deadurl = yes | url = http://www.aruba.com/holloway/taskforce.htm | title = The Strategic Communications Task Force | accessdate = 2006-04-22 | date = 2006-04 | publisher = Government of Aruba | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20060422042748/http://www.aruba.com/holloway/taskforce.htm }}</ref>。该工作组还发布新闻稿并派代表接受媒体采访，同阿鲁巴政府一起反对抵制该岛的举动<ref name="Vanity" />。

=== 《菲尔医生》播映的录像带以及随后的法律诉讼 ===
2005年9月15日，《[[菲尔医生_(电视节目)|菲尔医生]]》（{{lang|en|''Dr. Phil''}}）节目中出现采访迪帕克·卡尔珀（{{lang|en|Deepak Kalpoe}}）的视频片段，这段视频是用隐藏镜头摄制，显示卡尔珀回答：“她做了，你都想不到有多容易”，意指霍洛威同卡尔珀兄弟及范德斯洛特三人都发生了性关系<ref name="CBS News 2005-10-06" />。这段录像由私家侦探杰米·斯克特斯（{{lang|en|Jamie Skeeters}}）提供，在电视上播映后许多媒体都预测当局会再度逮捕几名嫌疑人，多姆皮格当时也称只要录像带合法，卡尔珀兄弟和范德斯洛特就很可能会再度被捕<ref name="dompigreaction" />。

阿鲁巴警方随后找出更加完整的视频版本，但卡尔珀在视频中的说法同《菲尔医生》节目中的说法不符，很显然电视上的版本断章取义，曲解了当事人的原意<ref name="CNN 2005-12-01">{{cite news | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160306214406/http://transcripts.cnn.com/TRANSCRIPTS/0512/01/ng.01.html | archivedate = 2016-03-06 | url = http://transcripts.cnn.com/TRANSCRIPTS/0512/01/ng.01.html | title = Nancy Grace – What Did Deepak Kalpoe Tell Investigators? (Transcript) | accessdate = 2016-06-06 | date = 2005-12-01 | publisher = Fox News Channel | quote = SKEETERS: Nobody told her that you can't (DELETED) her – you know? I mean, and I'm sure she had sex with all of you and (INAUDIBLE) KALPOE: No, she didn't. }}</ref>。为阿鲁巴政府工作的某位非正式发言人兼评论员称，录像带显示卡尔珀摇头并称“没有，她没做”，否认霍洛威曾与他和另外两名男子发生性关系。另据{{lang|en|[[MSNBC|MSNBC]]}}报导，视频中最关键的字眼根本听不清，主持人丽塔·考斯比（{{lang|en|Rita Cosby}}）质疑卡尔珀是否真的说过《菲尔医生》节目版本视频中那些话<ref>{{cite news | title = Rita Cosby Live & Direct | accessdate = 2016-06-06 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160306131508/http://www.nbcnews.com/id/10281941/ns/msnbc-rita_cosby_specials/t/rita-cosby-live-direct-nov-th/ | date = 2005-12-01 | publisher = NBCNews.com | quote = You know, Clint, are we ever going to know sort of what those words are?  And do you think it's something that the FBI—my understanding is—when Jamie was on this show, he did say that the FBI had just picked up the tape.  I think that was about a week or two ago.  Why don't we hear from the FBI to sort of settle this out? | deadurl = no | url = http://www.nbcnews.com/id/10281941/ns/msnbc-rita_cosby_specials/t/rita-cosby-live-direct-nov-th/ | archivedate = 2016-03-06 }}</ref>。

2006年12月，卡尔珀一家在洛杉矶以诽谤罪起诉《菲尔医生》节目和斯克特斯（斯克特斯于2007年1月去世）<ref name="LA Times 2007-06-04" /><ref name="lawsuit">{{cite news | date = 2007-06-02 | publisher = Fox News Channel | url = http://www.foxnews.com/story/2007/06/02/judge-tosses-wrongful-death-lawsuit-in-holloway-case.html | title = Judge tosses wrongful death lawsuit in Holloway case | accessdate = 2016-06-06 | archivedate = 2016-03-06 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160306195323/http://www.foxnews.com/story/2007/06/02/judge-tosses-wrongful-death-lawsuit-in-holloway-case.html }}</ref>。贝丝·特威蒂和戴夫·霍洛威于是也向同一法院提起诉状，以过失致人死亡罪控告卡尔珀兄弟。2007年6月1日，法院以缺乏个人司法管辖权为由拒绝受理过失致人死亡罪诉讼<ref name="lawsuit" />，诽谤罪原计划在2011年10月12日开庭审理<ref name="SFGate 2011-05-05">{{cite news | agency = Associated Press | url = http://www.sandiegouniontribune.com/news/2011/may/05/judge-oks-trial-against-dr-phil-in-holloway-suit/ | title = Judge Oks trial against Dr. Phil in Holloway suit | accessdate = 2016-06-06 | date = 2011-05-05 | archivedate = 2016-06-06 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160606080932/http://www.sandiegouniontribune.com/news/2011/may/05/judge-oks-trial-against-dr-phil-in-holloway-suit/ | newspaper = The San Diego Union-Tribune | deadurl = no }}</ref>，之后又延迟到2015年4月<ref>{{cite news | title = Dr. Phil, CBS Gain Advantage in Defamation Lawsuit Over Natalee Holloway Show | author = Eriq Gardner | url = http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/thr-esq/dr-phil-cbs-gain-advantage-688038 | date = 2014-03-12 | accessdate = 2016-06-06 | deadurl = no | archivedate = 2016-03-02 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160302152325/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/thr-esq/dr-phil-cbs-gain-advantage-688038 }}</ref>。贝丝和戴夫还曾在保卢斯和约兰·范德斯洛特父子抵达纽约期间向该市法院起诉两人，法院于2006年8月决定不予受理，理由是司法审判地不便<ref name="lawsuit2">{{cite news | archivedate = 2016-03-06 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160306132106/http://www.cbsnews.com/news/natalee-mom-crushed-by-legal-setback/ | url = http://www.cbsnews.com/news/natalee-mom-crushed-by-legal-setback/ | title = Natalee mom 'crushed' by legal setback | accessdate = 2016-06-06 | date = 2006-08-05 | publisher = CBS News }}</ref>。

2005年11月10日，保卢斯·范德斯洛特在起诉阿鲁巴政府不正当拘禁的官司中获胜，摆脱犯罪嫌疑人身份的同时，还得以追回之前获得的政府合同<ref name="timeline1" />。保卢斯接下来更进一步，要求政府对他的不当逮捕向他和家人提供经济补偿<ref name="UPI 2006-08-04">{{cite news| archivedate = 2009-07-19 | deadurl = yes | url = http://www.caribbeannetnews.com/cgi-script/csArticles/articles/000026/002632.htm | title = Holloway suspect's father awarded damages in Aruba | accessdate = 2008-03-08 | date = 2006-08-04 | agency = [[合众国际社|UPI]] | newspaper = Caribbean Net News | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20090719213240/http://www.caribbeannetnews.com/cgi-script/csArticles/articles/000026/002632.htm }}</ref><ref name="AP 2006-08-08">{{cite news | agency = Associated Press | date = 2006-08-08 | title = Aruban Prosecutors to Appeal Order to Pay Damages to Paulus Van Der Sloot | publisher = Fox News Channel | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20120510205005/http://www.foxnews.com/topics/paulus-van-der-sloot.htm | deadurl = yes | accessdate = 2012-05-10 | url = http://www.foxnews.com/topics/paulus-van-der-sloot.htm | archivedate = 2012-05-10 }}</ref>。下级法院支持原告立场，但损失赔偿裁决被上级法院推翻<ref name="Expatica 2007-02-15">{{cite news | title = No damages in Holloway case | url = http://www.expatica.com/nl/news/No-damages-in-Holloway-case_142719.html | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160606083201/http://www.expatica.com/nl/news/No-damages-in-Holloway-case_142719.html | date = 2007-02-15 | publisher = Expatica | archivedate = 2016-06-06 | deadurl = no | accessdate = 2016-06-06 }}</ref>。

=== 阿米格欧新闻的报导 ===
2007年7月，阿米格欧新闻网发文报导对伦弗洛和多姆皮格的采访。两人称，阿鲁巴当局在案件调查过程中受到美方官员的系统性阻挠。同时失踪案发还不到一天，就有“{{lang|en|medjet}}”医疗转运飞机未经当局许可飞抵阿鲁巴，并在岛上停留数天，准备在找到霍洛威后立即带她飞离阿鲁巴，不再知会当局。<ref name="Amigoe">{{cite news | title = The other side of the Holloway-case: 'Police Aruba hindered by FBI' | date = 2007-07-03 | publisher = Amigoe}}</ref>伦弗洛还称，她和贝丝曾于2005年6月2日接到神秘女性来电，要求贝丝以金钱换取女儿所在地址，宣称是霍洛威不想和母亲回去。伦弗洛接下来同另一个美国人一起带着钱到达某个吸毒及贩毒人员频繁活动的房屋，之前的消息称霍洛威就在这里，但他们到场后却发现尤格·特威蒂已经抵达，在周围“引起骚动和恐慌”，最终他们都一无所获。<ref name="Amigoe" />特威蒂一家否认伦弗洛的说法，贝丝谴责伦弗洛就是个“女巫”<ref name="Vanity" />。

=== 改编电影 ===
2009年4月19日，根据贝丝·霍洛威《挚爱娜塔莉》一书改编的[[电视电影|电视电影]]《[[娜塔莉·霍洛威_(电影)|娜塔莉·霍洛威]]》（{{lang|en|''Natalee Holloway''}}）在[[LMN_(电视频道)|终身电影联播网]]播出<ref name="UPI 2008-10-07">{{cite web | title = Lifetime planning Natalee Holloway movie | date = 2008-10-07 | agency = United Press International | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160303212234/http://www.upi.com/Entertainment_News/2008/10/07/Lifetime-planning-Natalee-Holloway-movie/UPI-71421223415829/ | archivedate = 2016-03-03 | deadurl = no | accessdate = 2016-06-06 | url = http://www.upi.com/Entertainment_News/2008/10/07/Lifetime-planning-Natalee-Holloway-movie/UPI-71421223415829/ }}</ref>。片中娜塔莉·霍洛威一角由[[艾米·古麦尼克|艾米·古麦尼克]]（{{lang|en|Amy Gumenick}}）饰演，[[特蕾西·波伦|特蕾西·波伦]]（{{lang|en|Tracy Pollan}}）出演贝丝·霍洛威（贝丝·特威蒂），[[格兰特·秀|格兰特·秀]]扮演乔治·“尤格”·特威蒂，雅克·斯特瑞多姆（{{lang|en|Jacques Strydom}}）饰演约兰·范德斯洛特。电影是在南非摄制，剧情上主要再现2005年娜塔莉·霍洛威失踪当晚的事件及之后的调查过程。<ref>{{cite news | work = USA Today | publisher = Gannett | title = Pollan plays Natalee Holloway's mother | url = http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/life/television/news/2009-03-12-pollan-natalee-holloway_N.htm | date = 2009-03-12 | author = Gary Strauss | accessdate = 2016-06-06 | archivedate = 2016-03-16 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160316165545/http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/life/television/news/2009-03-12-pollan-natalee-holloway_N.htm }}</ref>

电影中的悬案同样未破，并根据不同嫌犯及证人的证词反复设想案发当晚的实际情况，这其中就包括范德斯洛特的证词。节目首播时共吸引320万观众收看，[[尼尔森收视率|尼尔森收视率]]创下电视台成立11年来新高。<ref name="Variety/Kissel 2009-04-20">{{cite news | last = Kissel | first = Rick | date = 2009-04-20 | title = Lifetime Movie scores with 'Holloway | work = [[综艺_(杂志)|Variety]] | accessdate = 2016-06-06 | archivedate = 2016-04-11 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160411121548/http://variety.com/2009/scene/markets-festivals/lifetime-movie-scores-with-holloway-1118002635/ | publisher = Penske Business Media | url = http://variety.com/2009/scene/markets-festivals/lifetime-movie-scores-with-holloway-1118002635/ }}</ref>影片所获评论褒贬不一，《[[伯明翰新闻报|伯明翰新闻报]]》（{{lang|en|''The Birmingham News''}}）的亚历克·哈维（{{lang|en|Alec Harvey}}）称影片既凌乱又不平衡，虽然这起悲剧让美国持续关注数月之久，但搬上荧光屏后却让人过目即忘<ref name="Harvey 2009-04-17">{{cite news | last = Harvey | first = Alec | date = 2009-04-17 | title = 'Natalee Holloway' a disappointing TV movie | newspaper = The Birmingham News | accessdate = 2016-06-06 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160303203734/http://blog.al.com/aharvey/2009/04/natalee_holloway_a_disappointi.html | url = http://blog.al.com/aharvey/2009/04/natalee_holloway_a_disappointi.html | archivedate = 2016-03-03 }}</ref>。不过，{{lang|en|[[PopMatters|PopMatters]]}}网站的杰克·米尼（{{lang|en|Jake Meaney}}）认为电影表现的“冷静和清醒”令人称奇，并称赞特蕾西·波伦在片中的出色演出<ref name="PopMatters-review">{{cite web | last = Meaney | first = Jake | date = 2010-01-22 | title = Review: Natalee Holloway | accessdate = 2016-06-06 | work = PopMatters | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160307081319/http://www.popmatters.com/review/118543-natalee-holloway/ | archivedate = 2016-03-07 | url = http://www.popmatters.com/review/118543-natalee-holloway/ }}</ref>。

== 传媒报道 ==
[[File:NataleeHollowayWall-NewsCrews.jpg|thumb]]。]]

[[美国无线电视网列表|美国各大电视联播网]]都为这起失踪案投入大量节目时间，详细报导搜索、案件调查及相关传闻。在所有花费大量时间报导事件的电视人中，又以福克斯新闻频道《[[与格蕾塔·范叙斯特伦一起记录在案|记录在案]]》（{{lang|en|''On the Record''}}）节目主持人格蕾塔·范叙斯特伦（{{lang|en|Greta Van Susteren}}）和{{lang|en|[[CNN|CNN]]}}[[头条新闻台|头条新闻台]]的南希·格雷斯最具影响。范叙斯特伦几乎连续不断地报导案件，令《记录在案》收视率创下历史新高，至今仍未打破<ref name="SPTimes 2005-08-22">{{cite news |quote=On the Record with Greta Van Susteren, who is averaging more than 2-million viewers a night, up almost 60 percent from a year ago. |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304125910/http://www.sptimes.com/2005/08/22/Worldandnation/From_paradise_to_para.shtml |url=http://www.sptimes.com/2005/08/22/Worldandnation/From_paradise_to_para.shtml |title=From paradise to paradox in Aruba |accessdate=2016-06-06 |date=2005-08-22 |publisher=St. Petersburg Times |archivedate=2016-03-04 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>。格雷斯的节目则成为[[头条新闻台|头条新闻台]]黄金时段的王牌节目，每晚都会在黄金时段播出两期，其中一期现场直播，另一期为重播。随着案情陷入胶着，人们的关注点大多转移到贝丝·特威蒂和她发表的声明上。<ref name="NBC/Kosinski 2005-08-24">{{cite news | last = Kosinski | first = Michelle | date = 2005-08-24 | title = How mom keeps spotlight on the Holloway case | publisher = NBC News | accessdate = 2016-06-07 | url = http://www.nbcnews.com/id/9065827 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160305104134/http://www.nbcnews.com/id/9065827/ | archivedate = 2016-03-05 | deadurl = no }}</ref>阿鲁巴政府发言人特拉朋伯格对此称：“案件仿佛到了显微镜下，全世界都在关注<ref name="lighton" />。”

大量的媒体报导也引来评论界反弹，称这是“[[失踪白人女性综合症|失踪白人女性综合症]]”的典型体现，即媒体对白人女性失踪案的关注度要远远超过白人男性或有色人种失踪案。{{lang|en|CNN}}批评其它电视台用大量时段报导事件，但其中却没有什么新的内容，{{lang|en|CNN}}新闻主播[[安德森·库珀|安德森·库珀]]称如此大量的报导实在“荒谬透顶”。<ref name="CNN 2005-08-11">{{cite news | title = Anderson Cooper 360° – Transcript (Aired August 11, 2005 – 19:00 ET) | date = 2005-08-11 | publisher = CNN | accessdate = 2016-06-06 | url = http://transcripts.cnn.com/TRANSCRIPTS/0508/11/acd.01.html | quote = We decided to start tracking their coverage, because to be honest, it's getting downright ridiculous. – Cooper | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20150908221245/http://transcripts.cnn.com/TRANSCRIPTS/0508/11/acd.01.html | deadurl = no | archivedate = 2015-09-08 }}</ref>

政治评论员兼专栏作家[[阿里安娜·赫芬顿|阿里安娜·赫芬顿]]曾在案发后不久表示，“如果观众完全只是从电视上获得消息，那么他们会以为国家现在面临的首要问题就是有个叫娜塔莉的18岁女孩在阿鲁巴失踪了。要是出现这类新闻（比如说[[迈克尔·杰克逊|迈克尔·杰克逊]]又怎么了之类），我就会在事情结束后想，终于可以松口气儿了，现在咱们来点真正的新闻吧，但我们偏偏就是记不住教训。”<ref name="BBC News 2005-06-25" />

2008年3月，《阿鲁马日报》发文称，拉丁裔失踪案的关注度往往无法持续，这类案件通常也不会得到其他族裔失踪案那么高的关注度和那么多的资源。比如说，英语媒体往往更关注失踪白人女性的故事，比如娜塔莉·霍洛威在阿鲁巴失踪一案。但要是拉丁裔或[[非裔美国人|非裔]]女性失踪，即使是有报导，人们也未必会看到她们的脸。<ref name="Latin">{{cite news | title = Justice for Reyna Isabel | date = 2008-03-17 | newspaper = El Diario}}</ref>

[[CBS_(电视网)|CBS电视网]]资深记者丹娜·沃克（{{lang|en|Danna Walker}}）认为，虽然有批评称这起案件之所以会成为新闻只不过是因为当事人是漂亮的白人女性，新闻工作者应该把注意力转移到别的地方，发掘别的新闻。但实际上并非如此，“这是大新闻，美国女孩在历险时失踪了，再也没有回来。这是很大的谜团，人们会认同这点。”<ref name="BBC News 2005-06-25" />

《[[早安美国|早安美国]]》节目主播[[克里斯·科莫|克里斯·科莫]]（{{lang|en|Chris Cuomo}}）认为他在节目中对霍洛威案的大量报导并无不妥：“我觉得自己无权去评判观众想看什么……如果他们说：‘我想知道这女孩怎么了’……那我也想帮他们找到答案。”<ref name="Cuomo">{{cite news | title = News anchor picks a different forum to make a difference | date = 2008-05-07 | newspaper = The Washington Post}}</ref>

霍洛威的家人认为媒体对此案的报导力度还不够强。美国媒体对这起失踪案的报导一度饱和，但到了2005年8月下旬，来势汹汹的[[2005年飓风卡特里娜|飓风卡特里娜]]开始大量占据报导空间。<ref name="KatrinaCloak" /><ref name="DHolloway 2006, p. 124">{{cite book | last1 = Holloway | first1 = Dave | first2 = R. Stephanie | last2 = Good | first3 = Larry | last3 = Garrison | date = 2006-04 | title = Aruba: The Tragic Untold Story of Natalee Holloway and Corruption in Paradise | url = https://archive.org/details/arubatragicuntol0000holl | publisher = Thomas Nelson | location = Nashville, TN | isbn = 978-1-59555-063-7 | oclc = 63472537 | pages = [https://archive.org/details/arubatragicuntol0000holl/page/124 124], 150 | quote = Hurricane Katrina had left the door open for the boys to be sent on their way with little publicity and few restrictions because it took the world's focus off of Natalee, but only for a brief time. The huge amount of publicity had waned and, during that time of quiet for us, Joran and the Kalpoe brothers were sent home … All of the news shows that had followed our every move only a day before had now become fixated on the next big ratings grabber: the victims of Hurricane Katrina.}}</ref>贝丝·特威蒂和戴夫·霍洛威声称，正是这场飓风令阿鲁巴当局有了喘息的机会，所以才会释放嫌犯<ref name="KatrinaCloak" />。但是，约兰·范德斯洛特羁押司法审查的截止日期在飓风来袭很久前便已确定<ref name="timeline1" />。

戴夫·霍洛威在同他人合著的书中感叹：

{{quote|本来全世界都在关注娜塔莉，但飓风卡特里娜改变了这点，虽然持续时间不长，但仍为约兰和卡尔珀兄弟打开了回家的大门……昨天，所有的新闻节目都在追踪我们的一举一动，但现在一切都变了，都在紧盯下一个收视率高峰：飓风卡特里娜的受害者<ref name="DHolloway 2006, p. 124" />。}}

